description.plain:
ITA

Kina, nome d'arte di Pasquale Renella, è un produttore italiano classe ‘99, originario di Acerra (NA).

Nel 2017 rilascia il suo EP d'esordio roses, mentre nel marzo dell'anno successivo pubblica il brano “Get You the Moon”, cantato da Snøw, che ottiene un successo virale a livello internazionale e lo porta a firmare per la Columbia Records.




ENG

Pasquale Renella (born 1999), better known by his stage name Kina, is a producer from Acerra, Italy.

In 2017, Kina released his self-issued debut EP, roses. In March of 2018, he released his breakout single ”Get You The Moon,” featuring singer Snøw. Soon after the viral success of the record, Kina signed with Columbia Records.

songs.title: Get You the Moon

description.plain:
“Get You the Moon” is a collaborative single between Snøw and Kina that details an individual who’s deeply in love with another person. The individual decides to sing this song as a tribute for everything they’ve gone through together.

The song is an expression of the adoration Kina feels towards the person the narrator is singing to. In other words, the narrator loves this individual so much that if he had the wherewithal he would give him or her the moon.
